{"type":"message","id":"c3c1a466","parentId":"09432ed7","timestamp":"2026-06-02T02:40:56.025Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This doesn't seem to be in the project codebase at all. Let me think about what this error actually means.\n\nThe URL decodes to something like:\n- App: `wx2af2be9a3b47ff43` (a WeChat Mini Program appid)\n- Path: `pages/reward-center/index`\n- env: release\n- Query params: `activityKey=YYZY_CCG_JOIN_WECOM&gameId=5199&key=<encrypted_key>`\n\nThis looks like it's trying to open a WeChat Mini Program via a deep link (`weixin://dl/business/`). The `[ERROR]` suggests something went wrong when trying to open this URL.\n\nPossible issues:\n1. The URL is too long - the key parameter is quite large (encrypted/bloated)\n2. The URL scheme `weixin://` isn't being handled correctly on the platform\n3. The encoded URL has issues with special characters (note the `%2f` vs `%2F` inconsistency, or potential double-encoding)\n4. The Mini Program jump failed for some reason\n\nWithout finding the source code, I can only make educated guesses. Let me try one more search approach.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BW0JSrPwsqmf9g7J3AHy0075","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\**\\*.lua' -Pattern 'wechat|WeChat|微信|weixin' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 20\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":85,"output":373,"cacheRead":21888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22346,"cost":{"input":0.000011900000000000001,"output":0.00010444000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000612864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000729204}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780368052512,"responseId":"41247f4c-30e8-4e73-b3e8-168ae9921c11"}}
